<paragraph id="8BB1D67CFFE81E2983BDFE280103881B" blockId="26.[151,684,474,839]" pageId="26" pageNumber="85">
Plants 
<quantity id="4CF67B99FFE81E29820CFE2802568AA8" box="[256,367,474,501]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="26" pageNumber="85" unit="cm" value="40.0" valueMax="60.0" valueMin="20.0">20-60 cm</quantity>
high, stem subterranean or reaching 
<quantity id="4CF67B99FFE81E2983F7FE090279894F" box="[251,320,505,532]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="26" pageNumber="85" unit="cm" value="35.0">35 cm</quantity>
above ground; corm with a crescent-shaped basal ridge. Leaves 3-6, lower 1 basal, narrowly 4-grooved, sheathing below, 
<quantity id="4CF67B99FFE81E29815CFDC40195890C" box="[592,684,566,593]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="26" pageNumber="85" unit="mm" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1-2 mm</quantity>
diam.; outer bracts with hardly visible membranous margins, inner bracts submembranous with wide colorless or brown-marked membranous margins. Flowers orange-yellow with dark lines in the cup, unscented, tepals oblanceolate, 
<quantity id="4CF67B99FFE81E298134FD22019289B6" box="[568,683,720,747]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="26" pageNumber="85" unit="mm" value="25.0" valueMax="30.0" valueMin="20.0">20-30 mm</quantity>
long; filaments 
<quantity id="4CF67B99FFE81E298240FD1C02918854" box="[332,424,750,777]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="26" pageNumber="85" unit="mm" value="6.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="5.0">5-7 mm</quantity>
long, anthers 
<quantity id="4CF67B99FFE81E29815DFD1C01958854" box="[593,684,750,777]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="26" pageNumber="85" unit="mm" value="6.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="5.0">5-7 mm</quantity>
long. Fruiting peduncles sharply curved, later erect. Flowering: Aug.-Sep. — 
<figureCitation id="1335CAF9FFE81E2982E8FCDE010F881B" box="[484,566,813,839]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="20.[114,142,1666,1683]" captionTargetBox="[130,1196,204,1630]" captionTargetId="graphics-13@20.[114,1195,92,1807]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Fig. 2. — Flowers of Romulea species: A, R. tabularis; B, R. saldanhensis; C, R. tortuosa; D, R. sabulosa; E, R. eximia; F, R. sulphurea; G, R. namaquensis; H, R. komsbergensis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5180123" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5180123/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="85">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB1D67CFFE81E2983BDFC9901748F06" blockId="26.[151,684,873,1115]" pageId="26" pageNumber="85">
<taxonomicName id="4C0EADFFFFE81E2983BDFC9902A588D8" box="[177,412,874,900]" class="Liliopsida" family="Iridaceae" genus="Romulea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="26" pageNumber="85" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="saldanhensis">
<emphasis id="B97A0A6EFFE81E2983BDFC9902A588D8" box="[177,412,874,900]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="85">Romulea saldanhensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a narrow endemic of the Western Cape coast between 
<collectingCountry id="F31996ECFFE81E29810BFC7A014388FF" box="[519,634,905,931]" name="Saint Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha" pageId="26" pageNumber="85">St. Helena</collectingCountry>
Bay and Darling and occurs on seasonally wet granitic flats. It is allied to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0EADFFFFE81E29826BFC36028388BC" box="[359,442,965,992]" class="Liliopsida" family="Iridaceae" genus="Romulea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="26" pageNumber="85" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="flava">
<emphasis id="B97A0A6EFFE81E29826BFC36028388BC" box="[359,442,965,992]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="85">R. flava</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in its single basal leaf and submembranous inner bracts and is distinguished mainly by the consistently large flowers of a deep, golden yellow or orange color quite different from the lemon yellow of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0EADFFFFE81E2982F9FBB3017F8F07" box="[501,582,1088,1115]" class="Liliopsida" family="Iridaceae" genus="Romulea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="26" pageNumber="85" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="flava">
<emphasis id="B97A0A6EFFE81E2982F9FBB3013C8F05" box="[501,517,1088,1113]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="85">R</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B97A0A6EFFE81E29811FFBB2017F8F07" box="[531,582,1089,1115]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="85">flava</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
